		<Update>
			<Where Tag="TXT_KEY_MISSION_CULTURE_BOMB_DISABLED_COOLDOWN"/>
			<Set Text="You have created a Great Work recently, and may not do so again for another {1_Num} turns."/>
		</Update>
		<Update>
			<Where Tag="TXT_KEY_SPECIALISTSANDGP_CULTUREBOMB_ADV_QUEST"/>
			<Set Text="What does the great work special ability do?"/>
		</Update>
		<Update>
			<Where Tag="TXT_KEY_SPECIALISTSANDGP_CULTUREBOMB_HEADING4_BODY"/>
			<Set Text="A Great Artist can create a Great Work in any tile inside or adjacent to your territory. Great Works created [COLOR_POSITIVE_TEXT]inside cities[ENDCOLOR] give you a large amount of [ICON_CULTURE] Culture.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Great Works [COLOR_POSITIVE_TEXT]outside cities[ENDCOLOR] give you ownership of the target tile and all six surrounding it. Great Works outside cities will &quot;flip&quot; foreign territory to your territory, but it won't flip a foreign city (although the foreign city may suddenly find itself surrounded by your terrain). Flipping foreign terrain is not an automatic act of war, though some civilizations will no doubt find the act offensive. Note that another artist can flip the terrain back at a later point - there's no limit to the frequency or number of times that a tile can flip during a game."/>
		</Update>
		<Update>
			<Where Tag="TXT_KEY_SPECIALISTSANDGP_CULTUREBOMB_HEADING4_TITLE"/>
			<Set Text="Special Ability: Create Great Work"/>
		</Update>
		<Update>
			<Where Tag="TXT_KEY_MISSION_CULTURE_BOMB"/>
